summary: This document is a submission from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York to Judge Wang, presenting an application for a search warrant, four referenced exhibits, and a proposed search warrant. The agent is available to swear out the warrant, indicating an active investigative step in the Epstein case.

persons.name: Judge Wang

persons.name: Assistant United States Attorney

events.title: Submission of Search Warrant Application
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney submits an application for a search warrant, along with four exhibits and a proposed warrant, to Judge Wang for consideration.

locations: I St. Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: A search warrant application related to the Epstein case was submitted to Judge Wang on October 27, 2020.
The application included four referenced exhibits and a proposed search warrant.
The submitting official is an Assistant United States Attorney from the Southern District of New York.
The agent involved was available to swear out the warrant on the afternoon of submission or the following morning.
